# React

- Always type your state getters & setters using TypeScript
- Always implement in the easiest, most straightforward way possible
- Avoid unnecessary complexity
- Only use `useMemo` when absolutely necessary
- Only use `useCallback` when absolutely necessary
- Only use `ref`, `useRef` and `forwardRef` when absolutely necessary

- Always use anonymous functions
- Always use `async` and `await` instead of legacy promises

## Timing & State Management
- Never use `setTimeout` as a hack or workaround for timing issues
- If you need `setTimeout` to make state updates work, the architecture is wrong
- Instead, fix the root cause by:
  - Combining related state updates into a single atomic operation
  - Using proper dependency arrays in useEffect
  - Moving logic into state management (e.g., Zustand store actions)
  - Using proper event handlers and callbacks
  - Or ask the user if you are unsure

## Next.js usage
- To render an image in HTML, always use `<img />` instead of `<Image />`
